WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:06.470
And we are retracing the steps of the Children of Israel, their epic journey from Egypt to the Promised Land.

00:07.171 --> 00:15.301
And in that process, we're taking a look at how that parallels our walk in the Christian life and what we can learn from that.

00:16.062 --> 00:26.094
And one of the things I've been encouraging you to do, and I'll just remind you again, is as we go through this series in keeping with this whole idea of going on the trip, that you keep a travel log.

00:26.635 --> 00:29.138
And by that I mean do some writing.

00:29.250 --> 00:33.334
be reading on your own at home, the story of Israel's trek through the wilderness.

00:33.934 --> 00:41.742
And as you read that, be praying and ask the Lord, what can I learn that applies to my life, my own journey with you?

00:41.802 --> 00:47.688
And write those things down as we go, and I would love to hear some of the things that you're observing.

00:47.788 --> 00:49.790
I got an email this week.

00:50.310 --> 00:56.296
It was not directly on show of Israel, but it was just a really beautiful reflection on God being at work in our lives.

00:56.636 --> 00:58.418
And I know others of you,

00:58.530 --> 01:01.193
God's been giving you some good stuff in these last few weeks.

01:01.293 --> 01:04.196
I would love to see what you have been learning and thinking about.

01:05.618 --> 01:10.984
We started this study by considering the implications of the first Passover.

01:11.064 --> 01:13.107
What got Passover started, right?

01:13.207 --> 01:22.638
It was that night of terrible judgment on the Egyptians who had steadfastly refused to release the enslaved people of Israel.

01:22.678 --> 01:26.482
But it was also this night of divine protection.

01:26.978 --> 01:35.807
God delivered his people and they were protected from the destroyer and they were protected because they put their faith in God's promise to them.

01:36.948 --> 01:38.209
A lamb was sacrificed.

01:38.870 --> 01:46.457
You recall it was the lamb's blood that marked the doorway to their homes and those within those houses were safe that night.

01:47.418 --> 01:55.186
And we talked about the fact that the Christian life begins with this act of faith in the supreme lamb of God in Jesus.

01:55.906 --> 02:04.134
And then we consider that next major event last week, we looked at Israel's escape from Egypt and specifically that miraculous crossing of the Red Sea.

02:04.174 --> 02:09.580
And that deliverance from Egypt's power had involved two things, right?

02:09.640 --> 02:12.183
The first was the saving blood of the Lamb.

02:12.823 --> 02:18.849
And the second was the crossing over the Red Sea, something that they were not able to accomplish without God's intervention.

02:18.869 --> 02:23.474
It required a miracle of God for them to actually escape the land of slavery.

02:24.034 --> 02:31.905
And yet Israel still had to choose to obey and move from where they were to take the way of escape that God had given them.

02:32.766 --> 02:42.279
We talked about the fact that in the same way the Christian has brought into a new life by the power of the substitutionary death of Jesus on the cross.

02:43.441 --> 02:50.290
And inherent in that is also this call to cross over, to leave behind the things that have enslaved us and then

02:50.370 --> 02:54.675
in faith to step into a life of obedience to Jesus.

02:55.916 --> 03:00.762
And yet our steps of faith are merely a response to God's grace in making a way.

03:00.822 --> 03:12.656
We talked last week about the morality river and that as hard as you might want to cry and stroke across on your own, swim on your own and make your way to the other side, none of us can do it perfectly.

03:13.477 --> 03:18.002
And just like the children of Israel, there comes a point where we have to say, Lord, unless you make a way

03:18.178 --> 03:26.909
there is no way for me to cross over on my own and that gift of salvation is something that God makes available freely to us because of his grace.

03:28.331 --> 03:46.994
Now today we're going to take a look at a third foundational part of Israel's journey through the wilderness and it's something that we skipped over as we were talking about moving from Passover to the Red Sea Crossing and yet it was essential both in their escape from Egypt as well as their entire journey in the Promised Land.

03:47.618 --> 03:51.403
Today we're gonna take a look at the fiery cloud that led the way.

03:52.204 --> 03:53.906
Let me take you to Exodus chapter 13.

03:54.707 --> 04:02.478
And the Lord went before them by day in a pillar of cloud to lead them along the way.

04:02.518 --> 04:09.587
And by night in a pillar of fire to give them light that they might travel by day and by night.

04:10.448 --> 04:17.618
The pillar of cloud by day and the pillar of fire by night did not depart from before the people.

04:19.010 --> 04:23.878
Now, if you read this story, you'll find that the cloud appears even before the people have crossed the Red Sea.

04:24.680 --> 04:35.819
In chapter 14, it's recorded that the fiery cloud stood guard between Pharaoh's army and the people of Israel the night before they made that crossing of the Red Sea.

04:37.201 --> 04:40.927
The fullest description that we get of it, because it raises lots of questions.

04:40.968 --> 04:41.649
What was this?

04:41.689 --> 04:44.754
We get a fuller description later in their journey.

04:44.994 --> 04:51.161
At this point in the journey where we're going to read this description, they actually have built the tabernacle.

04:51.461 --> 04:57.868
This beautiful tent, a portable temple, if you will, that traveled with them.

04:58.669 --> 05:02.753
And that tent itself was full of symbolism.

05:03.714 --> 05:09.560
Someday I think I'll probably do a sermon series just on the tabernacle because it's fascinating to examine all the things that were in it.

05:11.022 --> 05:14.866
That tabernacle was always set up in the middle of the camp.

05:15.010 --> 05:18.255
all of the tribes surrounded with the tabernacle in the center.

05:18.395 --> 05:23.764
And it symbolically said, God stands at the center of who we are as a people.

05:24.986 --> 05:32.037
Right alongside that highly symbolic tent and actually resting over it was what I'm calling the fiery cloud.

05:32.357 --> 05:34.301
This comes out of Numbers chapter 9.

05:34.341 --> 05:42.834
On the day that the tabernacle was set up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, the tent of the testimony.

05:43.298 --> 05:47.363
And in evening, it was over the tabernacle like the appearance of fire until morning.

05:48.205 --> 05:49.166
So it was always.

05:49.687 --> 05:53.351
The cloud covered it by day and the appearance of fire by night.

05:54.833 --> 05:59.199
Whenever the cloud lifted from over the tent, after that, the people of Israel set out.

05:59.840 --> 06:03.525
And in the place where the clouds settled down, there the people of Israel camped.

06:04.526 --> 06:10.194
At the command of the Lord, the people of Israel set out, and at the command of the Lord, they camped.

06:11.298 --> 06:14.981
As long as the cloud rested over the tabernacle, they remained in camp.

06:15.942 --> 06:23.349
Even when the cloud continued over the tabernacle many days, the people of Israel kept the charge of the Lord and did not set out.

06:24.891 --> 06:32.017
Sometimes the cloud was a few days over the tabernacle, and according to the command of the Lord, they remained in camp.

06:32.037 --> 06:34.960
Then, according to the command of the Lord, they set out.

06:35.701 --> 06:38.223
And sometimes the cloud remained from evening until morning.

06:38.984 --> 06:41.266
And when the cloud lifted in the morning, they set out.

06:41.730 --> 06:46.076
or if it continued for a day and a night, then the cloud lifted, they set out.

06:48.018 --> 07:00.535
Whether it was two days or a month or a longer time that the cloud continued over the tabernacle abiding there, the people of Israel remained in camp and did not set out, but when it lifted, they set out.

07:01.937 --> 07:11.570
At the command of the Lord they camped, and at the command of the Lord they set out, they kept the charge of the Lord at the command of the Lord by Moses.

07:12.514 --> 07:14.296
So what was that all about?

07:16.278 --> 07:20.662
I don't know about you, but when I read about this, I have just so many questions.

07:22.363 --> 07:26.888
What exactly did this pillar of cloud and fire look like?

07:28.169 --> 07:30.591
I mean, get a little hint from the text and numbers.

07:30.671 --> 07:38.018
We're told that it covered the tabernacle by day, and that the cloud says it had the appearance of fire by night.

07:39.119 --> 07:42.002
And that's why we're referring to it as a fiery cloud.

07:42.498 --> 07:56.975
My sense is that it wasn't necessarily a blazing fire tornado, if you will, but that at night, this cloud, what had been a cloud by day, had its own glow.

07:57.075 --> 08:01.660
We talk about sometimes at night, you'll see the clouds lit up at night, we'll say the clouds were on fire.

08:02.081 --> 08:09.810
And that's kind of my sense, that at night, this cloud, you realize it had its own internal light emanating from it.

08:10.530 --> 08:18.642
I don't think that takes away from the fire metaphor at all because God was still revealing His presence in a way that's best described as fire.

08:19.543 --> 08:25.432
Fire is a metaphor in Scripture that the Scripture returns too often to describe God's presence and His holiness.

08:26.854 --> 08:29.518
Another question I have is how big was this thing?

08:30.138 --> 08:31.621
I mean, how big was the cloud?

08:31.681 --> 08:34.605
How big was this fiery cloud before them?

08:35.827 --> 08:38.130
It appears it was large enough

08:38.274 --> 08:43.681
to have provided a protective barrier between the encampment of Israel and the army of Egypt.

08:43.761 --> 08:55.876
So I would take it, that was pretty big, but also appears, been large enough both to serve as a leading beacon to several thousand people and even provide illumination if they traveled at night.

08:55.956 --> 08:58.019
So again, that sounds pretty big.

08:59.340 --> 09:07.250
But then you also find, as you read the story, descriptions of the cloud standing at the doorway to the tent of meeting.

09:07.586 --> 09:12.010
which sounds like something a lot smaller, a lot more compact.

09:13.512 --> 09:18.957
And so my sense is that the size of the cloud varied to fit the situation.

09:20.218 --> 09:22.380
Leading the nation, big cloud.

09:23.161 --> 09:25.423
Marking the tenant meeting, small cloud.

09:26.324 --> 09:28.326
Same cloud, just different size.

09:29.988 --> 09:36.434
More important than some of the logistical questions that we might have about the cloud, I think scripture invites us to ponder

09:36.674 --> 09:40.519
Why the Lord chose to manifest His presence in this way?

09:41.320 --> 09:46.406
Why this pillar of cloud by day and this fiery pillar at night?

09:48.168 --> 09:54.756
One of the things that God never permitted Israel to do was to create an image to represent Him.

09:56.859 --> 10:05.970
A consistent, critique you'll find in scripture of pagan nations was that they served gods that they had made with their own hands.

10:06.402 --> 10:07.964
You'll find this in the prophets.

10:08.905 --> 10:10.147
Others talk about this.

10:10.187 --> 10:15.614
The foolishness to bow down and worship something that you have carved with your own hands.

10:16.255 --> 10:21.803
And the troll of Israel were never allowed to create an image of God.

10:22.884 --> 10:29.533
Any God that you can reduce to an art piece has to be a God of limited scope.

10:30.554 --> 10:33.298
A God that can be somehow controlled or manipulated.

10:34.338 --> 10:39.405
The idol worshiping nations usually had multiple gods because no single god could do everything.

10:40.366 --> 10:41.909
They all were limited in scope.

10:41.969 --> 10:50.781
There were gods of war and goddesses of fertility, gods of thunder, gods of wine, and gods of just about any other especially that you could imagine.

10:51.702 --> 10:59.954
And each of them was carved or cast or painted with a specific look that tried to tell you what this particular god was good at.

11:00.482 --> 11:02.585
Think about the gods of the Greek and Romans.

11:03.086 --> 11:03.887
You've got Zeus.

11:04.007 --> 11:04.548
Remember Zeus?

11:04.568 --> 11:10.416
He's got the thunderbolts in his hand, the god of thunder, or Hermes, the messenger of the gods.

11:11.017 --> 11:14.142
He's the one that had wings on his feet to help him go faster.

11:14.202 --> 11:19.670
Or Medusa, who had the lovely hairdo of writhing snakes.

11:20.691 --> 11:22.213
Or Artemis.

11:22.714 --> 11:28.242
I remember when Paul went to Ephesus, that's where they made a lot of the images of Artemis, and they realized

11:28.354 --> 11:34.402
that as Paul was preaching about Jesus and people were turning to Jesus, they were turning away from the worship of Artemis.

11:34.962 --> 11:36.344
And that's what led to the riot.

11:36.905 --> 11:44.234
They were afraid, the trades were afraid that their business was gonna be ruined if people stopped buying images and idols of Artemis.

11:44.935 --> 11:47.718
Well, Artemis was a goddess of fertility.

11:48.580 --> 11:56.850
And because of that, the image of Artemis, you can look these statues up online easily enough, Artemis is covered in breasts.

11:57.346 --> 11:59.528
because she's the goddess of fertility.

12:01.050 --> 12:07.556
The tabernacle that eventually sat at the middle of the Israelite encampment was full of its own kind of art.

12:07.656 --> 12:20.609
There were lots of artistic pieces there, and they all symbolically spoke to different aspects of who God was and what he was doing among his people, but there was no image of God himself.

12:21.830 --> 12:25.874
The only symbol that spoke directly to God's presence

12:26.146 --> 12:31.214
was the fiery cloud that descended and rested over the tabernacle.

12:32.856 --> 12:37.023
When you think about clouds, clouds are ethereal, aren't they?

12:38.325 --> 12:40.448
Have you ever tried to grab hold of a cloud?

12:41.770 --> 12:47.078
I remember the first time I got to fly in an airplane, I thought, wow, what's it going to be like to fly through a cloud?

12:48.220 --> 12:50.483
Well, you just kind of went through the cloud.

12:50.544 --> 12:53.568
You couldn't really wrap your hands around it.

12:53.628 --> 12:54.770
And so in one sense,

12:54.882 --> 12:57.827
A cloud is almost nothing.

12:58.849 --> 13:00.572
And yet, it's not.

13:01.494 --> 13:07.524
In fact, I had the chance years ago to do part of ground school, the friend of mine.

13:08.446 --> 13:10.930
Unfortunately, he got a job change, and I never got to finish it.

13:11.932 --> 13:13.996
But this is the private pilot manual.

13:14.677 --> 13:19.986
And right there I've marked where there is a whole section in this manual about clouds.

13:20.802 --> 13:39.305
Now here we're talking about planes that are worth hundreds of thousands of dollars and sophisticated instruments and all of the things that go into flight and yet we had to spend time learning about clouds because clouds can have a big effect on a flight because there's a lot of power that can be held in the cloud.

13:39.805 --> 13:46.994
You watch any storm as it is building and you realize clouds can represent something incredibly powerful.

13:49.410 --> 13:51.714
Clouds can be a source of violent storms.

13:51.874 --> 13:53.637
Clouds are uncontrollable.

13:55.159 --> 13:57.623
Since God is saying, that is me.

13:59.065 --> 14:02.751
In some ways, you can't wrap your hands around me, but I am everywhere.

14:03.592 --> 14:04.734
And I am powerful.

14:06.637 --> 14:08.099
Fire, why fire?

14:09.381 --> 14:15.410
Cloud that glowed in blazing fiery color at night, it reminded Israel that God was always present.

14:15.970 --> 14:21.857
And that fire, it speaks to purity and power and illumination and a living force.

14:23.779 --> 14:27.303
You think about the relationship of that fiery cloud and the tabernacle.

14:28.244 --> 14:33.089
When it came time to move, the priest would pack up the tabernacle with all of its symbolism.

14:34.450 --> 14:35.852
But you can't pack up a cloud.

14:37.394 --> 14:39.876
It wouldn't fit in any bags for going on the trip.

14:39.977 --> 14:42.379
All you could do was you could follow it.

14:43.340 --> 14:44.882
And even on the darkest night,

14:45.346 --> 14:49.833
When God wanted his people to move, it was his illumination that showed the way.

14:51.395 --> 14:55.041
The fiery cloud was always present showing them the way.

14:57.785 --> 15:01.090
So what do we make of this fiery cloud?

15:03.193 --> 15:11.986
Well, eventually Israel came to their promised land and in place of a mobile tabernacle, they were able to erect a fixed temple.

15:12.738 --> 15:19.627
And again, the temple was filled with symbols, but it did not contain any depiction of God himself.

15:20.828 --> 15:24.232
Here's the account of Solomon's dedication of the newly completed temple.

15:24.252 --> 15:25.975
This comes from 2 Chronicles 7.

15:28.338 --> 15:38.010
As soon as Solomon finished his prayer, fire came down from heaven and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices and the glory of the Lord filled the temple.

15:38.771 --> 15:41.554
And the priest could not enter the house of the Lord

15:41.794 --> 15:45.319
because the glory of the Lord filled the Lord's house.

15:46.942 --> 16:03.947
So there was a temple, it was a beautiful temple, Solomon had built it, the finest materials, and yet what mattered more was the manifest presence of the Lord, a presence that was manifested in fire and something that was described as the glory of the Lord.

16:05.830 --> 16:11.538
Something visible but ethereal that

16:11.778 --> 16:12.759
filled the temple.

16:15.162 --> 16:22.291
Something that was not man-made and yet it was substance to them enough that it says the priest could not enter.

16:24.394 --> 16:26.957
It was a glorious holy cloud.

16:29.020 --> 16:30.922
That's interesting in the temple ever after.

16:30.982 --> 16:33.846
There was a flame that was kept constantly burning there.

16:34.767 --> 16:40.434
It was a symbol, a reminder that God's spirit was always present with them.

16:41.378 --> 17:04.786
Now if you move on from the book of Exodus and this account in Chronicles and you get to the book of Acts, we get into the New Testament, if in the death of the Lamb of Passover we find a picture of Jesus dying in our place, rescuing this from the curse of death, and if in the resurrection we find the promise that a way has been opened for us to cross over from death to life,

17:05.186 --> 17:19.980
just as Israel by God's miraculous power crossed over from slavery into a journey of freedom, then on Pentecost, I think we once again find the fiery cloud descending to lead God's people on a journey.

17:22.062 --> 17:23.583
Here's what we find in Acts chapter two.

17:25.305 --> 17:30.150
When the day of Pentecost arrived, they, that is the disciples, were all together in one place.

17:31.111 --> 17:34.834
And suddenly, there came from heaven a sound like a mighty rushing wind

17:35.234 --> 17:43.667
and it filled the entire house where they were sitting and divided tongues as of fire appeared to them and rested on each one of them.

17:45.670 --> 17:47.373
Do you see what's happening in the symbolism?

17:48.795 --> 17:58.610
The assurance to the nation of Israel that God was with them was the appearance of a pillar of fire to illuminate the night in a cloud to lead them.

17:59.938 --> 18:12.614
The evidence of God's presence first in the wilderness tabernacle and later in the temple of Jerusalem was the fire falling from God to consume the sacrifices and this glory cloud of his presence filling the tabernacle.

18:14.897 --> 18:21.425
The ongoing symbolic reminder in the temple of God's presence was an eternal flame that burned brightly.

18:23.067 --> 18:28.594
But now for the people who have put their faith in the blood of God's perfect lamb,

18:29.570 --> 18:33.574
and who have willingly chosen to follow him into a new life journey.

18:34.956 --> 18:42.885
The fire comes to rest not on a tabernacle or on a temple, but it rests on individuals.

18:44.026 --> 18:45.027
Do you see the shift there?

18:47.270 --> 18:52.255
You remember how that fiery cloud and wilderness was sometimes huge and sometimes small.

18:52.976 --> 18:56.159
It manifested itself proportionate the occasion.

18:56.640 --> 18:58.482
And on the day of Pentecost,

18:59.138 --> 19:03.242
the fire manifested itself in very personal proportions.

19:03.963 --> 19:07.427
It came to rest on each one of the believers gathered there.

19:09.629 --> 19:16.557
In these opening experiences of Israel's journey out of Egypt, I think we see evidence really of the Triune God.

19:18.339 --> 19:28.850
We see God the Father displaying his power as Moses obediently raises his staff as the plagues fall, as the Red Sea is parted,

19:30.146 --> 19:34.912
God the Son is foreshadowed in the saving death of the Passover Lamb.

19:36.594 --> 19:42.461
And God the Holy Spirit is revealed in the fiery cloud as He leads the people on their journey through the wilderness.

19:44.603 --> 19:49.169
So what does the story of Israel and the fiery cloud have to teach us on our own journey?

19:49.770 --> 19:53.114
Fascinating what that meant for the children of Israel, what does it mean for us?

19:55.016 --> 20:00.082
Well first I would say if you are a follower of Jesus, one of the messages is

20:00.258 --> 20:01.720
You are not alone.

20:03.282 --> 20:06.967
Israel was never alone on their journey through the wilderness.

20:08.269 --> 20:14.357
No matter how confusing it might be, no matter the dangers they might face, the cloud was always there.

20:14.958 --> 20:16.320
God was always with them.

20:17.141 --> 20:25.272
The message on the day of Pentecost is that the Holy Spirit has come to each believer, and we are not alone.

20:27.495 --> 20:29.618
In some of his final words of encouragement,

20:29.794 --> 20:36.343
and instruction to his disciples, Jesus spoke of the Holy Spirit's coming in his ministry, this from John 16, 13.

20:37.044 --> 20:41.950
When the spirit of truth comes, he will guide you into all truth.

20:43.312 --> 20:46.276
Now that promise had special application to the disciples.

20:47.037 --> 20:53.786
We see it unfolding all through the book of Acts, but we also recognize the Holy Spirit gives guidance to all who follow Jesus.

20:55.248 --> 20:59.634
I was talking to a friend recently regarding a worship song they'd heard, a new one that had come out,

21:00.450 --> 21:02.592
And she said there was one lion that bothered her.

21:03.554 --> 21:04.655
And maybe you've heard this song.

21:05.276 --> 21:09.020
It says, this one lion says, we need another Pentecost.

21:10.381 --> 21:16.328
And what struck her was, we don't need another Pentecost.

21:16.348 --> 21:17.550
Pentecost has happened.

21:18.531 --> 21:20.493
The Holy Spirit has come.

21:21.574 --> 21:24.818
We're not still waiting and hoping that God sends His Spirit.

21:25.038 --> 21:28.402
The Spirit has come and He has stayed with God's people.

21:29.250 --> 21:34.335
You don't need a temple or a priest or even a pastor to connect you with God.

21:35.536 --> 21:40.121
His spirit is pleased to dwell in us as Jesus' people.

21:40.962 --> 21:50.391
1 Corinthians 3, 16 says, do you not know that you are God's temple and that God's spirit dwells in you?

21:51.111 --> 21:57.778
You know, Israel didn't have to ask for or earn the fiery cloud.

21:58.658 --> 22:03.624
In fact, as we'll see, they were frequently described as being stiff-necked people.

22:04.565 --> 22:07.608
You want to talk about people who deserved God's favor.

22:07.668 --> 22:09.410
These folks weren't them.

22:09.470 --> 22:13.875
The fiery cloud was not their reward.

22:15.157 --> 22:16.558
It was God's gift to them.

22:18.180 --> 22:23.246
Not even the disciples in that upper room had to ask for the Holy Spirit.

22:23.306 --> 22:26.930
Jesus simply told them to go and pray and wait.

22:27.906 --> 22:31.130
but they really had no idea exactly what they were waiting for.

22:32.953 --> 22:36.317
And those guys were not all paragons of faith either, were they?

22:37.278 --> 22:47.812
I mean, it was Peter who not too many days prior had denied even new Jesus, or Thomas who made himself famous ever since for being the doubter.

22:49.635 --> 22:55.282
But we're told even when Jesus ascended that there were some of them who saw that happen, it says, and some doubted.

22:56.194 --> 23:01.941
So it's not that these guys had it all figured out that they were all so good, so faithful.

23:02.001 --> 23:05.845
The only thing they had done was simply to trust what Jesus said.

23:05.885 --> 23:12.012
He told them to go, to pray, to wait, they did, and God acted.

23:13.714 --> 23:22.404
And so I would just say that if you have placed your faith in Jesus, then God's Spirit is pleased to dwell in you.

23:23.525 --> 23:24.466
It is His gift.

23:25.282 --> 23:34.771
Not because you deserve it, not because you've earned it, not because you prayed hard enough to get it, but because God is pleased to pour His Spirit out on His people.

23:35.552 --> 23:38.074
And because of that, you are never alone.

23:39.936 --> 23:47.704
Second, I would say that our job is not to coax the Spirit to come, but rather to follow the Spirit where He leads.

23:48.985 --> 23:51.207
That was Israel's experience with the fiery cloud.

23:51.227 --> 23:52.889
When it moved, they moved.

23:52.989 --> 23:54.450
Where it moved, they went.

23:54.562 --> 23:56.745
And when it paused, they set up camp.

23:59.790 --> 24:03.396
So how do we experience a spirit-led life?

24:04.998 --> 24:09.926
I don't know about you, but there have certainly been times in my life when I would have welcomed a fiery cloud.

24:11.448 --> 24:13.952
Okay, Lord, what should I do now?

24:14.874 --> 24:22.706
And it would be lovely if I would look out the front door and there would be a fiery pillar stand in front yard that said, right this way, Tim,

24:24.258 --> 24:26.080
Now, wouldn't it be nice if you got up in the morning?

24:26.721 --> 24:28.603
And there it was, just waiting outside the front door.

24:29.404 --> 24:32.166
And all you had to do was follow it out to the car and off you went.

24:33.668 --> 24:36.791
You know, maybe your boss called and said, why haven't you shown up for work?

24:36.811 --> 24:39.374
He'd say, boss, I'm sorry, but the cloud hasn't moved your way yet.

24:39.735 --> 24:40.515
It's not my fault.

24:42.177 --> 24:48.544
Your wife asks, if you're going to get the lawn mode, and you let her know that you'll head to the mower just as soon as the cloud does, that would be kind of handy.

24:49.525 --> 24:51.147
It would probably speed some things up.

24:52.188 --> 24:54.130
It might not always be convenient.

24:54.754 --> 25:00.560
Sunday morning, 20 minutes before church, the cloud is sitting in the car honking the horn.

25:01.661 --> 25:02.322
It's time to go.

25:02.362 --> 25:05.425
You're trying to sleep in.

25:06.026 --> 25:09.149
The cloud keeps lighting up the room, saying it's time to get him to go to work.

25:09.189 --> 25:10.191
You gotta get out of bed.

25:11.432 --> 25:12.113
You need to pray.

25:12.133 --> 25:20.422
It could be both a blessing and an annoyance, but at least it'd be real clear where you were supposed to be every day.

25:21.803 --> 25:24.626
Unfortunately, the cloud was a one-time experience for Israel.

25:25.922 --> 25:29.105
God led and directed them all through the wilderness.

25:31.208 --> 25:34.191
And even after, but after the wilderness, it was in different ways.

25:34.231 --> 25:36.794
It was through prophets, kings, signs.

25:37.895 --> 25:43.481
And I'd say the Spirit is still leading us as well, but it's not a fiery cloud going ahead of a mass migration.

25:44.602 --> 25:46.644
It's a more intimate, personal encounter.

25:47.826 --> 25:52.070
The Apostle Paul described it being a walk.

25:52.090 --> 25:53.392
I like that terminology.

25:53.412 --> 25:55.474
I think because I grew up in

25:55.618 --> 26:12.040
An environment where oftentimes our sense of being in the spirit had to involve a lot of volume, a lot of excitement, a lot of getting the crowd really wound up.

26:12.801 --> 26:16.726
And then when Paul talks about a walk in the spirit, it's that he had a walk.

26:17.407 --> 26:25.458
It's this humble, progressive, day by day, step by step, movement of my heart and my attitudes and my actions.

26:26.210 --> 26:30.634
Here's how he described it in his letter to the church at Galatia, Galatians chapter five.

26:30.674 --> 26:38.241
I say walk by the spirit and you will not gratify the desires of the flesh.

26:39.442 --> 26:44.387
For the desires of the flesh are against the spirit and the desires of the spirit are against the flesh.

26:45.388 --> 26:50.273
For these are opposed to each other to keep you from doing the things you want to do.

26:50.313 --> 26:56.018
But if you are led by the spirit, you are not under the law.

26:57.282 --> 26:58.904
Now the works of the flesh are evident.

27:00.006 --> 27:15.006
Sexual immorality, impurity, sensuality, idolatry, sorcery, enmity, strife, jealousy, fits of anger, rivalries, dissensions, divisions, envy, drunkenness, orgies, and things like these.

27:16.128 --> 27:22.396
I warn you, as I warned you before, that those who do such things will not inherit the kingdom of God.

27:24.198 --> 27:26.802
But the fruit of the Spirit is love.

27:27.842 --> 27:38.918
joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, self-control.

27:38.958 --> 27:43.224
Against such things, there is no law.

27:44.605 --> 27:49.172
And those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires.

27:50.193 --> 27:56.402
If we live by this spirit, I love this phrase, let us also keep in step with the spirit.

27:57.378 --> 28:02.948
Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, and being one another.

28:05.131 --> 28:14.487
Paul says here, you get a pretty good idea as to whether or not you're following the leading the Holy Spirit, if you're staying in step with him by looking at the tracks that you're leaving.

28:15.970 --> 28:17.573
He talks about the works of the flesh.

28:19.035 --> 28:23.122
He says, if you're getting caught up in immoral sexual behavior,

28:24.354 --> 28:27.658
You find your heart being consumed with jealousy and anger.

28:29.221 --> 28:54.034
If you keep getting caught up in petty arguments with people, if you move from one interpersonal falling out to the next, if some of your habits, he talks about drunkenness, if you're drinking is getting to excess or any behavior that indicates that self-interest is winning out over true love, he says you can be sure that you are not being led by the Spirit.

28:56.194 --> 29:20.863
On the other hand, he says, if you find yourself choosing to turn away from anger, seeking the good of others, quieting your heart and seeking to love, even the people who offend you, says that it's a good indicator that in the wilderness of this world, you are being led by God's Spirit.

29:22.885 --> 29:23.666
So how are you doing?

29:24.930 --> 29:28.133
What kind of tracks did you leave behind this week?

29:30.355 --> 29:33.158
So how do we become better followers?

29:34.500 --> 29:38.043
Well, the first thing I would say is we need to pay attention.

29:39.164 --> 29:44.390
The children of Israel knew when to move because the fiery cloud rusted at the center of the accountment.

29:45.030 --> 29:48.494
And the fiery cloud didn't drive them, it led them.

29:49.254 --> 29:50.696
And that meant they had to pay attention.

29:51.737 --> 29:52.818
Where was it leading?

29:54.914 --> 29:58.578
You know, we are distracted people.

29:58.598 --> 29:59.819
So many distractions.

30:01.521 --> 30:10.131
If we want to be led by the Spirit, we need to choose disciplines in life that will put the Lord at the center of our attention.

30:11.893 --> 30:13.014
In fact, here's a fun experiment.

30:13.515 --> 30:23.666
You might think back over just the past week and ask yourself, how much time have you spent meditating on God's word, time spent in prayer?

30:23.970 --> 30:27.155
versus time spent watching news.

30:29.559 --> 30:32.464
Some of you get pretty wound up over the news.

30:33.425 --> 30:46.246
And when I hear how your personal life goes, I was no surprise because you're spending hours upon hours immersing yourself in a medium that is completely designed to keep you wound up.

30:48.169 --> 30:51.154
And if I try to find out, well, how much time have you actually spent in God's Word?

30:51.906 --> 30:57.254
Well, I mean, I read the three-minute daily bread a couple times this week.

30:57.935 --> 31:05.546
Say, well, no wonder you're having a hard time having a heart that's being led by the Spirit because you're a distracted person.

31:06.587 --> 31:11.314
You're paying attention to everything else except the things that matter most.

31:13.666 --> 31:18.632
If we want to be led by the spirit, we need to choose the disciplines that will put the Lord to the center of our attention.

31:18.672 --> 31:24.419
And one of the ways we do that is we choose a regular time to read and study God's word.

31:25.120 --> 31:31.167
Someone 19 says, your word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path.

31:33.210 --> 31:37.054
Second thing I would say is we need to prioritize the encampment.

31:38.436 --> 31:40.018
What I mean by that is

31:40.258 --> 31:44.284
giving time and attention to the gathering with other believers.

31:46.347 --> 31:53.638
The Holy Spirit has been poured out on each of us as individuals, but he has not done so to enable us to live lives in solitude.

31:54.720 --> 31:57.384
Israel followed the fiery cloud together.

31:57.424 --> 32:04.114
The apostles, as they waited for Pentecost, were told together to wait for the Spirit's outpouring.

32:05.090 --> 32:14.402
The Apostle Paul repeatedly tells churches that the Holy Spirit gives different gifts to different people for the express purpose of ministering to each other.

32:14.442 --> 32:20.210
The sum of the Spirit's gifts and leading individuals is greater than its parts.

32:21.531 --> 32:29.682
Hebrews 10, let us consider how to stir up one another to love and good works, not neglecting to meet together.

32:29.986 --> 32:36.176
as is the habit of some, but encouraging one another and all the more as you see the day drawing near.

32:38.199 --> 32:40.483
Put emphasis on the encampment.

32:41.785 --> 32:45.150
I was listening to a podcast yesterday regarding the church in Iran.

32:45.170 --> 32:47.974
They're talking about the revival that is happening in Iran.

32:48.014 --> 32:52.882
They now think there were over a million believers in Iran.

32:53.666 --> 32:56.770
God is doing some amazing things spiritually there.

32:57.031 --> 33:06.184
They said one of the things the authorities have become focused on, they've almost given up trying to put individual believers in prison because they're just too many, they don't have enough prison space.

33:06.744 --> 33:22.066
And so they're going after church leaders and after the gatherings because what they've recognized is it's Christians who gather together that grow, keep them isolated, they're not nearly as much trouble, but let them come together

33:22.786 --> 33:24.649
And God starts doing powerful things.

33:27.494 --> 33:30.499
Third thing I would say is give time to prayer.

33:32.202 --> 33:34.987
Not demanding prayer, but abiding prayer.

33:36.029 --> 33:37.551
And I'll tell you, this is one that I struggle with.

33:37.591 --> 33:40.937
It is real easy for me when I think about prayer to show up with my grocery list.

33:41.858 --> 33:44.263
Okay, God, here's the stuff I need you to do for me this week.

33:46.586 --> 33:48.690
You know, Moses didn't get up each morning

33:48.930 --> 33:54.698
grab a map and then approach the fiery cloud with his demands as to where they should be led for the day.

33:55.740 --> 33:57.022
And that's how some of us come to prayer.

33:57.062 --> 34:00.026
We treat prayer kind of like the GPS in our car.

34:00.827 --> 34:11.663
And when I get in the car and I punch in where I want to go, and then it's like, you know what, I'll let the GPS decide how best to get me there, but I'll still set the destinations.

34:11.683 --> 34:13.846
That's not how we seek the Spirit's guidance.

34:15.488 --> 34:16.690
The disciples worshiped

34:17.282 --> 34:19.104
and they waited on the Lord for His direction.

34:19.185 --> 34:23.390
And I think that waiting is oftentimes one of the most difficult things that we do in a Christian life.

34:23.450 --> 34:24.432
At least it is for me.

34:24.472 --> 34:32.042
Did you notice that sometimes Israel's fiery cloud stayed put for days or months or even longer?

34:32.082 --> 34:39.331
That's a hard thing when God puts you someplace and you feel like He's telling you, you just need to stay.

34:39.372 --> 34:41.234
You need to wait.

34:42.946 --> 34:45.310
You've probably heard me say this before, but I'll say it again.

34:45.350 --> 34:50.578
The difference between patience and passivity is a fine one.

34:51.559 --> 34:58.850
How do you tell the difference if you are being patient, waiting for God, or if you've just become a passive person that isn't moving?

35:00.012 --> 35:02.256
Why say the difference is, are you paying attention?

35:03.317 --> 35:07.964
See, patient people keep looking and saying, okay, Lord, what do you want me to do next?

35:08.886 --> 35:11.730
Passive people just get comfortable and say, I don't really care.

35:12.546 --> 35:15.970
You know, unless God rocks my boat, I'm not paying attention.

35:16.211 --> 35:17.893
Are you paying attention?

35:21.017 --> 35:25.883
The fourth thing I would say is we need to allow the spirit to surprise us.

35:28.466 --> 35:35.235
Some of you I know are really comfortable with the supernatural side of how God works.

35:36.516 --> 35:41.202
The idea that the spirit might at times lead us in unusual ways is no big deal.

35:42.018 --> 35:43.841
That's actually something you're really excited about.

35:43.861 --> 35:45.163
You look for often.

35:46.885 --> 35:50.811
Some of you I know have had, you've had dreams that have been really shaping.

35:52.313 --> 35:54.035
You've had distinct mental images.

35:54.075 --> 35:55.938
You know came via God's spirit.

35:56.018 --> 36:02.768
You've been helped by a trusted friend who felt that they'd received a word from the Lord for you and it was exactly what you needed.

36:04.030 --> 36:09.938
Others of us are a lot more comfortable with highly rational, tightly knit logic.

36:10.818 --> 36:20.912
We love the Lord, but we believe He guides us much more through good solid Bible study, and we don't really go for that kind of woo-woo stuff.

36:22.655 --> 36:24.277
And I can put myself in that camp.

36:24.818 --> 36:31.708
Now, I grew up in very charismatic circles, but quite honestly, I get uncomfortable when things get too woo-woo.

36:34.812 --> 36:36.274
I have seen the excesses.

36:36.802 --> 36:44.933
I've seen the errors that can happen when people begin to place an inappropriate emphasis on seeking supernatural science.

36:47.477 --> 36:55.888
For those of us who have seen the abuses, it is easily to simply shut ourselves down to anything intangible like that.

36:58.211 --> 37:06.162
But you know, both scripture and in my own experience has taught me that God's spirit cannot be put in a box.

37:08.898 --> 37:11.180
fiery clouds are not easily contained.

37:13.262 --> 37:17.286
Listening to this podcast last night about the revival happening in Iran.

37:17.366 --> 37:21.250
And one of the stories I shared was an Iranian couple who had lost everything.

37:21.290 --> 37:23.111
They'd been forced to become refugees.

37:24.012 --> 37:26.054
They had totally disparate of life.

37:26.174 --> 37:28.096
And they finally had the night.

37:28.136 --> 37:29.678
They said, tonight is our last night.

37:30.759 --> 37:32.901
Tomorrow, we're going to die together.

37:33.341 --> 37:34.562
They were going to take their lives.

37:35.743 --> 37:38.546
That night, unbeknownst to each other,

37:38.850 --> 37:41.273
They both had identical dreams about Jesus.

37:42.595 --> 37:52.267
The husband woke up so shaken by this dream, he went out and found a small home fellowship, a small Christian church he knew about, and gave his heart to Jesus.

37:53.308 --> 37:58.835
He came home, his wife can see that something has happened, they get talking, he says, well, I had this dream.

38:00.517 --> 38:03.481
She begins crying and says, well, I had exactly the same dream.

38:05.103 --> 38:07.666
Hey, say what you will, that's kind of on the woo-woo scale,

38:09.314 --> 38:10.436
But God can do that.

38:12.319 --> 38:17.047
Another couple that heard the gospel via a Christian Persian language website.

38:17.647 --> 38:19.791
And they gave their lives to Jesus.

38:19.811 --> 38:21.554
They became part of a home fellowship.

38:21.634 --> 38:22.916
They were excited.

38:22.956 --> 38:23.597
They were growing.

38:23.657 --> 38:24.779
And then their lease ran out.

38:25.520 --> 38:26.842
And they couldn't afford the new rent.

38:26.862 --> 38:29.487
And they had to move across town to a new apartment place.

38:29.527 --> 38:30.528
There were 10 apartments.

38:31.209 --> 38:34.375
And there was a barbecue held for everybody in the apartment building to get acquainted.

38:35.136 --> 38:36.498
And as they're having dinner,

38:36.706 --> 38:42.972
One of the guys in the table looks across at this man and says, what is it about you that is different from us?

38:43.012 --> 38:44.614
There's something different about you.

38:46.335 --> 38:50.660
And inside this guy just hears God's spirit say, tell him.

38:52.201 --> 38:58.067
Now you understand, they're living in a religiously authoritarian Muslim majority culture.

38:59.308 --> 39:02.251
He's scared, but there's a strong sense.

39:02.692 --> 39:03.092
Tell him.

39:04.293 --> 39:05.234
So he says, well,

39:06.242 --> 39:09.547
we have met Jesus and he has changed our lives.

39:11.089 --> 39:19.742
They go home, they actually lock and bolt the door and put the chain up because they're so terrified the secret police are gonna show up that night.

39:19.762 --> 39:24.029
At about 11 o'clock there's a knock at the door and they think this is it.

39:24.630 --> 39:28.255
We've been turned in, they cracked the door open and there's a neighbor standing there.

39:29.156 --> 39:30.478
Says, can I talk to you about Jesus?

39:31.620 --> 39:35.666
They invite him in by two o'clock the next morning that guy gives his heart to the Lord.

39:36.450 --> 39:38.432
The next afternoon, another neighbor comes to him.

39:39.033 --> 39:40.114
He thinks he's the only one.

39:40.154 --> 39:42.537
He says, could I talk to you about Jesus?

39:44.218 --> 39:51.026
Within a month, at least one member of every household in the apartment complex had come to faith in Jesus.

39:52.808 --> 39:56.311
Now, do you think God had a hand in moving them to a new apartment building?

39:57.312 --> 40:01.076
And promptings say, go ahead, tell them what I've done in your life.

40:03.479 --> 40:06.322
A majority of what Israel did was extremely

40:06.498 --> 40:08.381
normal.

40:08.521 --> 40:10.503
They walked day after day.

40:11.425 --> 40:12.606
They did not teleport.

40:12.686 --> 40:13.808
They did not levitate.

40:13.928 --> 40:15.270
They just walked.

40:17.473 --> 40:19.656
Moses was called on to settle disputes.

40:20.697 --> 40:26.045
In fact, he even had to appoint a whole judicial system to help people work out their civic affairs.

40:26.145 --> 40:27.827
It was pretty normal stuff.

40:28.468 --> 40:30.972
Good rational problem solving.

40:30.992 --> 40:32.754
They weren't using crystal balls.

40:33.762 --> 40:39.410
There were animals to be herded, there were children to be schooled, but there was also the fiery cloud.

40:40.711 --> 40:42.053
And it was anything but normal.

40:43.355 --> 40:52.307
Most of the trip was undertaken the same way every trip was undertaken, but leading them was something more, something that went beyond the natural world.

40:52.367 --> 40:57.374
It was the leading of God's spirit that impacted every step of the trip.

40:59.737 --> 41:03.602
And I say all that to say that part of being people led by the spirit

41:04.258 --> 41:10.708
does mean staying open and sensitive to the spirit's promptings in ways that may be supernatural.

41:12.210 --> 41:20.984
If you have an inner prompting, a dream, receive a word from a friend that they believe God has given them, don't write it off, but check it out.

41:22.706 --> 41:27.834
Paul told a Christian, he said, hey, if someone says they've got a word from the Lord, judge the spirits.

41:27.894 --> 41:30.258
You use some discernment there.

41:32.866 --> 41:37.974
But Paul, a pretty rational guy himself, didn't deny that things like that could happen.

41:38.034 --> 41:39.496
He just said they should be judged carefully.

41:41.579 --> 41:43.282
We saw this when we studied the book of Acts.

41:43.302 --> 41:47.868
There were times that Paul made travel plans, and they got changed by the Holy Spirit.

41:47.888 --> 41:48.850
This from Acts 16, 7.

41:49.831 --> 41:54.698
They attempted to go in Bithynia, but the Spirit of Jesus did not allow them.

41:55.840 --> 42:02.450
Luke doesn't explain exactly how Paul and company got that message, but it was clear to them that they were being divinely rerouted.

42:04.354 --> 42:08.720
So for myself, I have stolen a phrase that I first heard from Preston Sprinkle.

42:09.661 --> 42:13.747
He calls himself a small sea charismatic with the seat belt on.

42:16.030 --> 42:17.011
I think that's me.

42:17.632 --> 42:18.854
Maybe a three-point harness.

42:25.102 --> 42:25.863
Here's what I want to say.

42:27.666 --> 42:33.554
God's spirit is with us and in us.

42:35.202 --> 42:40.691
I believe he is willing and he is able to lead us just like he led the children of Israel.

42:42.333 --> 42:47.020
It probably won't be by fiery cloud, but he will lead us.

42:48.142 --> 42:49.424
He will lead us by his word.

42:50.706 --> 42:52.429
He will lead us through his people.

42:53.691 --> 42:59.821
And as we listen and as we watch carefully, sometimes he may lead us in surprising ways.

43:02.465 --> 43:03.346
But here's the question.

43:05.314 --> 43:07.297
Are we paying attention?

43:09.419 --> 43:09.780
Let's pray.

43:15.787 --> 43:22.756
Father, thank you for the story of Israel, that image of the fiery cloud going before them.

43:24.819 --> 43:33.330
Thank you even more for the image of Acts that your fire, your spirit came to rest on each one of your disciples.

43:34.850 --> 43:37.956
That promise that your spirit has been poured out on us.

43:39.458 --> 43:40.640
Not because we deserve it.

43:41.803 --> 43:43.926
Not because we've somehow weadled it from you.

43:45.690 --> 43:51.320
Because in your grace, you've been pleased to dwell with and in us as your people.

43:54.165 --> 43:55.567
But I pray that we would pay attention.

43:57.230 --> 43:59.314
Help our distracted hearts, Father, I pray.

44:00.578 --> 44:06.405
This world shouts so loudly and wants us to give it our allegiance and our full attention.

44:06.466 --> 44:11.432
Father, free us, I pray, from that kind of slavery.

44:11.492 --> 44:21.925
Give us hearts that hunger to know you, hearts that hunger to follow you, that the fruit of your spirit would be the things that people see in our life.

44:22.046 --> 44:28.594
I pray that we'd be the kind of people, that when we're sitting with neighbors at a dinner, they would look at us and say, what is this different about you?

44:29.538 --> 44:33.144
You don't seem to walk and live the same way that everybody else is living.

44:33.224 --> 44:33.845
What is it?

44:36.590 --> 44:49.151
And Lord, as we have those opportunities, give us hearts that are open and ready to listen to your spirit and willing to speak what we have found in Jesus.

44:51.575 --> 44:55.922
Give us eyes and ears and hearts that are attentive to you.

44:57.154 --> 45:09.082
that are open and willing, whether it means to patiently wait where we are, whether it is to get up and take a bold step of faith, Lord, may we walk in step with Your Spirit, I pray.

45:11.066 --> 45:13.051
And I ask these things in Jesus' name.

45:13.953 --> 45:14.354
Amen.

